{"title_page": "List of active separatist movements in Europe", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{original research|date=September 2017}}\n{{use British English|date=August 2011}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n\nThis is a '''list of currently active separatist movements in Europe'''. [[Separatism]] often refers to full political [[secession]],<ref>{{Citation | contribution-url = http://www.thefreedictionary.com/separatism | title = Free Dictionary | contribution = Separatism}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | contribution = Separatism | contribution-url = http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/separatism | last1 = Merriam | last2 = Webster | title = Dictionary}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | contribution = Separatism | publisher = Encyclopedia | contribution-url = http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1O999-separatist.html | title = The Oxford Pocket Dictionary of Current English | year = 2008}}</ref> though separatist movements may seek nothing more than greater [[autonomy]] or to be recognised as a [[national minority]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Harris| first = Jerry| title = The Nation in the Global Era Conflict and Transformation | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UQQujqyOJJIC&pg=PA320 | year = 2009| publisher = Brill | isbn = 978-90-04-17690-4 | page = 320}}</ref>\n\nWhat is and is not considered an [[Autonomism|autonomist]] or secessionist movement is sometimes contentious. Entries on this list must meet three criteria:\n# They are active movements with active members;\n# They are seeking greater autonomy or [[self-determination]] for a geographic region (as opposed to [[National personal autonomy|personal autonomy]]);\n# They are citizens/peoples of the conflict area and do not come from another country.\n\nUnder each region listed is one or more of the following:\n* ''De facto'' state (de facto entity): for [[Diplomatic recognition|unrecognized]] regions with de facto autonomy;\n* Proposed state: proposed name for a seceding sovereign state;\n* Proposed autonomous area: for movements towards greater [[Autonomous area|autonomy for an area]] but not outright secession;\n** De facto autonomous government: for governments with de facto autonomous control over a region;\n** Government-in-exile: for a [[Government in exile|government based outside of the region in question]], with or without control;\n** Political party (or parties): for political parties involved in a political system to push for autonomy or secession;\n** Militant organisation(s): for armed organisations;\n** Advocacy group(s): for [[Advocacy group|non-belligerent, non-politically participatory entities]];\n** [[Ethnic]]/[[ethno-religious]]/[[racial]]/[[Regionalism (politics)|regional]]/[[Religious organization|religious]] group(s).\n\nVarious ethnic groups in Europe are seeking greater autonomy or independence. In the [[European Union]] (EU), several of these groups are members of the [[European Free Alliance]] (EFA). In some cases, the group seeks to unify into a different state \u2013 in cases where this does not involve the creation of a new state entity, this is considered to be [[irredentism]]. Analogous irredentist movements are included in the [[list of active irredentist movements]].\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Azerbaijan==\n[[File:Location Nagorno-Karabakh en.png|thumb|left|upright=1|Location of Nagorno-Karabakh]]\n\n{{Main|Nagorno-Karabakh War}}\n\n;Breakaway state\n\n{{Flag|Nagorno-Karabakh}}\n*Ethnic group: [[Armenians]]\n** ''De facto'' state: {{Flag|Artsakh}}<ref name=\"armenian-weekly-2017-02-21\">{{cite news |title=Artsakh Votes for New Constitution, Officially Renames the Republic |url=http://armenianweekly.com/2017/02/21/artsakh-votes-for-new-constitution-officially-renames-the-republic/ |work=[[Armenian Weekly]] |date=21 February 2017 |access-date=15 June 2018 |df=dmy-all |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222223223/http://armenianweekly.com/2017/02/21/artsakh-votes-for-new-constitution-officially-renames-the-republic/ |archive-date=22 February 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Constitution\">{{cite web |url=http://nkr.am/en/constitution/9/ |title=Constitution |publisher=Nagorno Karabakh Republic Ministry of Foreign Affairs |accessdate=23 July 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023103331/http://www.nkr.am/en/constitution/9/ |archivedate=23 October 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>, Unification with {{flag|Armenia}}\n*** Political organisation: [[National Assembly (Artsakh)|Government of Artsakh]]\n*** Militant organisation: [[Artsakh Defense Army]]\n\n==Belgium==\n{| style=\"float:right\"\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n[[File:Communities of Belgium.svg|thumb|Communities:\n{{legend|#fab274|[[Flemish Community]]}}\n{{legend striped|#fab274|#f2536b|up=yes|Flemish and French Community}}\n{{legend|#f2536b|[[French Community of Belgium|French Community]]}}\n{{legend|#40bb6a|[[German-speaking Community of Belgium|German-speaking Community]]}}]]\n| valign=\"top\" |\n[[File:Regions of Belgium.svg|thumb|Regions:\n{{legend|#fab274|[[Flemish Region|Flanders]]}}\n{{legend|#2385d2|[[Brussels|Brussels-Capital]]}}\n{{legend|#f2536b|[[Wallonia]]}}]]\n|}\n\n{{Main|Partition of Belgium}}\n\n;Autonomist movements\n\n{{flag|German-speaking Community}}<ref name=\"De Groene Amsterdammer\">{{cite news |url=http://www.groene.nl/2008/33/de-triangelspeler-van-belgie |title=De triangelspeler van Belgi\u00eb: Duitstalig Belgi\u00eb |publisher=De Groene Amsterdammer |last1=De Vries |first1=J. |last2=Tielemans |first2=A. |date=2008-08-15 |language=Dutch |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927135349/http://www.groene.nl/2008/33/de-triangelspeler-van-belgie |archivedate=2011-09-27 }}</ref><ref name=\"De Morgen\">{{cite news |url=http://www.demorgen.be/dm/nl/5036/Wetstraat/article/detail/995456/2009/09/15/Duitstalige-Gemeenschap-wil-extra-bevoegdheden.dhtml |title=Duitstalige Gemeenschap wil extra bevoegdheden |work=[[De Morgen]] |date=2009-09-15 |language=Dutch }}</ref>\n* People: [[German language|German-speaking]]\n** Autonomous area: [[Eupen-Malmedy|Eastern Belgium]]\n*** Political parties: [[ProDG (Belgium)|ProDG]] (former [[European Free Alliance|EFA]] member), [[Partei f\u00fcr Freiheit und Fortschritt| Party for Freedom and Progress]], [[Christlich Soziale Partei (Belgium)|Christian Social Party]]\n\n{{flag|Flanders}} \n* People: [[Flemish people|Flemish]]\n** Autonomous area: [[Flanders]]\n*** Political parties: [[Flemish Movement]]\n\n{{flag|Wallonia}}\n* People: [[Walloon people|Walloons]]\n** Autonomous area: [[Wallonia]]\n*** Political parties: [[Walloon Movement]]\n\n;Secessionist movements\n{{Further|Partition of Belgium}}\n\n{{flag|German-speaking Community}}<ref name=\"De Groene Amsterdammer\">{{cite news |url=http://www.groene.nl/2008/33/de-triangelspeler-van-belgie |title=De triangelspeler van Belgi\u00eb: Duitstalig Belgi\u00eb |publisher=De Groene Amsterdammer |last1=De Vries |first1=J. |last2=Tielemans |first2=A. |date=2008-08-15 |language=Dutch |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927135349/http://www.groene.nl/2008/33/de-triangelspeler-van-belgie |archivedate=2011-09-27 }}</ref><ref name=\"De Morgen\">{{cite news |url=http://www.demorgen.be/dm/nl/5036/Wetstraat/article/detail/995456/2009/09/15/Duitstalige-Gemeenschap-wil-extra-bevoegdheden.dhtml |title=Duitstalige Gemeenschap wil extra bevoegdheden |work=[[De Morgen]] |date=2009-09-15 |language=Dutch }}</ref>\n* People: [[German language|German-speaking]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag_of_the_German_Community_in_Belgium.svg|25px]] [[Eupen-Malmedy|Eastern Belgium]], Unification with {{flag|Germany}}\n*** Political parties: [[ProDG (Belgium)|ProDG]] (former [[European Free Alliance|EFA]] member), [[Partei f\u00fcr Freiheit und Fortschritt| Party for Freedom and Progress]], [[Christlich Soziale Partei (Belgium)|Christian Social Party]]\n\n{{Main|Flemish Movement|Greater Netherlands}}\n{{flag|Flanders}} or [[Flemish Community]] (the latter includes {{flag|Brussels-Capital Region}})\n* People: [[Flemish people|Flemish]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flag|Flanders}}, Unification with the {{flag|Netherlands}}\n*** Political parties: [[New Flemish Alliance]] (member of the [[European Free Alliance]]), [[Libertair, Direct, Democratisch]], [[Vlaams Belang]] and [[Flemish-Socialist Movement]]\n*** Movements: [[Vlaamse Volksbeweging]] (VVB), {{Interlanguage link multi|Overlegcentrum van Vlaamse Verenigingen|nl}}, [[Taal Aktie Komitee]] and [[Voorpost]]\n\n{{Main|Walloon Movement|Rattachism}}\n{{flag|Wallonia}}\n* People: [[Walloon people|Walloons]]\n** Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Flag of Wallonia.svg}} [[Wallonia|Walloon Republic]], Unification with {{flag|France}}\n*** Political parties: [[Walloon Rally]]\n\n==Bosnia and Herzegovina==\n[[File:SAO BIH 1991 1992.png|thumb|200px|right|Serbian Autonomous Provinces from 1991-92, created in rebellion against the government of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[File:Later carrington cutillero.png|thumb|200px|Carrington-Cutillero plan in early 1992. Serbian cantons shown in red, Bosniak cantons shown in green, Croat cantons shown in blue.]]\n\n{{Main|Partition of Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n\n;Secessionist movements\n{{main|Proposed secession of Republika Srpska}}\n{{flag|Republika Srpska}}\n* People: [[Serbs of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n** Proposed state: unification with {{SRB}}\n*** Political organisation: [[National Assembly (Republika Srpska)|National Assembly of Republika Srpska]]\n*** Political parties: [[Alliance of Independent Social Democrats]], [[Serbian Democratic Party (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|Serbian Democratic Party]], [[Serbian Radical Party of Republika Srpska|Serbian Radical Party]], [[SRS \"Dr. Vojislav \u0160e\u0161elj\"]]<ref>{{cite book| title = Armed Peacekeepers in Bosnia| year = 2004 | publisher = Diane | isbn = 978-1-4289-1020-1| page = 122}}</ref>\n\n;Autonomist movements\n{{main|Croat entity in Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n{{flagicon image|Flag of the Croatian Republic of Herzeg-Bosnia.svg}} [[Croatian Community of Herzeg-Bosnia]]\n* People: [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Croatian Republic of Herzeg-Bosnia}}, as a refounded [[Croat entity in Bosnia and Herzegovina|third entity of Bosnia-Herzegovina]] (formerly unification with {{CRO}})\n*** Political organisation: [[Croatian National Assembly]]\n*** Political parties: [[Croatian Democratic Union of Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Croatian Democratic Union 1990]], [[Croatian Christian Democratic Union (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|Croatian Christian Democratic Union]]\n\n== Cyprus ==\n[[File:Cyprus districts named.png|thumb|150px|left|The northern areas of the island of Cyprus administered by Turkish Cypriots]]\n\n{{Main|Turkish invasion of Cyprus}}\n\n;De facto states\n\n{{flag|Northern Cyprus}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Turkish Cypriot]]\n* Proposed: {{Flagicon|TRNC}} [[Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]] ([[Foreign relations of Northern Cyprus#International recognition|Recognised by Turkey]]), Unification with {{Flag|Turkey}}\n** ''De facto'' state: {{Flagicon|TRNC}} [[Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]]\n*** Political organisation: [[Government of Northern Cyprus]]\n\n==Czech Republic==\n[[File:First Czechoslovak Republic.SVG|thumb|right|In 1928, Moravia was merged into Moravia-Silesia, one of four lands of Czechoslovakia, together with Bohemia, [[Slovakia#Czechoslovakia (1918\u20131939)|Slovakia]] and [[Carpathian Ruthenia#Subcarpathian Rus' (1919\u20131938)|Subcarpathian Rus]].]]\n\n;Autonomist movements\n\n{{flagicon image|Banner of arms of Moravia.svg}} [[Moravia]]\n* People: [[Moravians (ethnic group)|Moravian]]\n** Political parties: [[Moravan\u00e9]] (former EFA member),<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.cepsr.com/clanek.php?ID=101\n|title=Rise and Fall of Moravian Regionalist Parties\n|publisher=The International Institute of Political Science\n|author=Maxmili\u00e1n Strmiska\n|accessdate=10 April 2009}}</ref> [[Moravian Land Movement]] (EFA member)\n\n== Denmark ==\n[[File:Hovedstaden in Denmark.svg|thumb|right|Location of Bornholm in Region Hovedstaden.]]\n\n{{Main|Secession in Denmark}}\n{{Main|Faroese independence movement}}\n{{Main|Greenlandic independence}}\n\n{{hatnote|For movements in [[Greenland]], see [[List of active separatist movements in North America#Denmark|List of active separatist movements in North America]]}}\n\n{{Flag|Bornholm}}\n* People: [[Danes|Bornholmsk]]\n** Proposed autonomous region/state: [[Bornholm]]\n*** Political party: [[Bornholm's Self-Government Party]] (''Bornholms selvstyreparti'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fritbornholm.proboards.com/thread/5|title=Free Bornholm|publisher=|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kmdvalg.dk/av/2001/a429.htm|title=Amtsradsvalg|publisher=|accessdate=4 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n{{Flag|Faroe Islands}}\n* People: [[Faroese people|Faroese]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flag|Faroe Islands|name=Republic of the Faroe Islands}}\n*** Political parties: [[Republican Party (Faroe Islands)|Republican Party]], [[Progress (Faroe Islands)|Progress]], [[People's Party (Faroe Islands)|People's Party]], [[Centre Party (Faroe Islands)|Centre Party]], [[Self-Government Party (Faroe Islands)|Self-Government Party]]\n*** Movement: [[Faroese independence movement]]\n\n==Finland==\n{{flag|\u00c5land}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ahvenanmaan itsen\u00e4isyytt\u00e4 ajavan puolueen johtaja: Suomesta tulossa yh\u00e4 enemm\u00e4n yksikielinen: 'Pienill\u00e4 askelilla ruotsi suljetaan pois' |trans-title= |last=Gr\u00e5sten |first=Hanna |work=Iltalehti |date=12 June 2018 |access-date=19 October 2019 |url= https://www.iltalehti.fi/kotimaa/a/201806082200989649 |language=fi }}</ref>\n* People: \u00c5land Swedes\n** Proposed state: {{flag|\u00c5land}}, or unification with {{flag|Sweden}}\n*** Political party: [[Future of \u00c5land]] (EFA member)\n\n==France==\n{{Main|Secession in France}}\n{{see also|List of active separatist mo