]], [[Aran Amassa]]\n\n{{Flagdeco|Flanders}} [[Flanders]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liberation.fr/france-archive/2008/07/07/le-college-change-de-nom-le-principal-est-menace-par-les-extremistes-flamands_75830}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.flandrepresse.fr/pays-de-flandre/societe-alors-que-la-catalogne-sembrase-la-flandre-francaise-sinterroge-sur-elle-meme}}</ref>\n{{Main|Flemish nationalism}}\n* People: [[Flemings]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagdeco|Flanders}} [[French Flanders]], [[Pale of Calais]] and [[Audomarois]] and re-unification with [[West Flanders]], [[East Flanders]], [[Tournaisis]] and [[Zeelandic Flanders]] into an independent Flemish state, Unification with the {{flag|Netherlands}}\n*** Political party: [[Flemish movement]]\n\n{{Flag|Provence}}\n* People: [[Provence|Proven\u00e7als]] (Occitans)\n** Proposed state: {{Flagdeco|Provence}} Provence\n*** Militant group: [[National Liberation Front of Provence|Front Nacionala Liberacion de Proven\u00e7a]]\n\n{{Flag|Catalonia|name=Northern Catalonia}}\n* People: [[Catalans|Northern Catalans]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flag|Catalonia|name=Catalonia}} or Unification with {{Flag|Catalonia|name=Catalan Countries}}\n*** Political parties: [[Republican Left of Catalonia|Esquerra Republicana- Catalunya del Nord]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://locals.esquerra.cat/catalunyanord|title=Catalunya del Nord|website=locals.esquerra.cat|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>, [[Oui au Pays Catalan]] (autonomist)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/el-nou-partit-oui-au-pays-catalan-opta-pel-regionalisme-i-la-renuncia-a-la-llengua-catalana/|title=El nou partit 'Oui au Pays Catalan' opta pel regionalisme i la ren\u00fancia a la llengua catalana|website=VilaWeb|language=ca|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n*** Advocacy organisations: [[Assemblea Nacional Catalana|Catalunya Nord per la independ\u00e8ncia]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://assemblea.cat/index.php/organitzacio/assemblees-territorials/catalunya-nord/catalunya-nord-per-la-independencia/|title=Catalunya Nord per la independ\u00e8ncia|website=Assemblea Nacional Catalana|language=ca|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>, [[\u00d2mnium Cultural|\u00d2mnium Catalunya Nord]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omnium.cat/ca/seus/catalunya-nord/|title=Catalunya Nord|website=\u00d2mnium Cultural|language=ca|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n*** Youth organisations: [[Young Republican Left of Catalonia|Joventuts d'Esquerra Republicana (Catalunya Nord)]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://joventrepublica.cat/regionals/catalunyanord|title=Joventuts d'Esquerra Republicana|website=joventrepublica.cat|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><br />\n;Autonomist movements\n\n{{Flag|Alsace}}\n{{main|Alsace independence movement}}\n* People: [[Alsatians (people)|Alsatians]] (Allemanics)\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flag|Alsace}}\n*** Political parties: [[Alsace d'Abord|Elsass Zuerst]], [[Nationalforum Elsass-Lothringen]], [[Unser Land]] (EFA member)\n\n{{Flagdeco|Brittany}} [[Brittany (administrative region)|Brittany]]\n* People: [[Bretons]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flagdeco|Brittany}} [[Brittany (administrative region)|Brittany]]\n*** Political party: [[Union D\u00e9mocratique Bretonne|Unvaniezh Demokratel Breizh]] (EFA member)\n\n{{Flag|Corsica}}\n* People: [[Corsicans]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Corsica}}\n*** Political party: [[Partitu di a Nazione Corsa]] (EFA member)\n\n{{Flag|Alpes-Maritimes}}\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flagicon image|Comte de Nice flag.svg}} [[County of Nice]]\n*** Political party: [[Partit Nissart]] ([[:fr:Parti ni\u00e7ois|Parti ni\u00e7ois (fr)]])<ref>{{Citation | url = http://www.partinicois.com/ | title = Parti ni\u00e7ois | language = fr |trans-title=Nice party}}</ref>\n\n{{Flagdeco|Bourgogne-Franche-Comt\u00e9}}  [[Bourgogne-Franche-Comt\u00e9]]\n* People: [[French people|French Burgundians]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flag|Burgundy}}\n*** Movement: Burgundian National Movement\n\n{{Flagicon image|Flag of Basse-Normandie.svg}} [[Normandy]]\n* People: [[Normans]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flagicon image|Flag of Basse-Normandie.svg}} [[Normandy]]\n*** Political party: [[Mouvement Normand|Mouvement normand]]\n\n{{Flagdeco|Savoy}} [[Savoy]]\n* People: Savoyans\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flagdeco|Savoy}} [[Savoy]]\n*** Political party: [[Savoy Region Movement|Movement R\u00e8gion Savou\u00e8]] (EFA member)\n\n{{Flag|Occitania}}\n* People: [[Occitans]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flag|Occitania}}\n*** Political parties: [[Partit Occitan]] (EFA member)\n\n{{flagdeco|Ardennes}} [[Ardennes]]\n* People: [[Ardennais (people)|Ardennais]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Ardennes}}\n*** Political party: [[Mouvement ardennais]]\n\n[[Vall\u00e9e de Chevreuse|Chevreuse High Valley]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lagazette-sqy.fr/2019/05/15/votreville/coignieres/vers-une-integration-partielle-de-la-commune-au-pnr/}}</ref>\n*People : Yvelinois\n**Proposed autonomous area: [[Vall\u00e9e de Chevreuse|Chevreuse High Valley]] ({{Flag|Yvelines}} and {{flag|Essonne}})\n***Organization: [[Front de lib\u00e9ration de la Haute Vall\u00e9e de Chevreuse]]\n\n==Georgia==\n{{Main|Occupied territories of Georgia}}\n{{see also|List of active separatist movements in Asia#Georgia}}\n\n[[File:Map of Georgia with Abkhazia and South Ossetia highlighted.svg|thumb|right|250px|Georgian administrative divisions are outlined in black. Russian-occupied territories ([[Abkhazia]] and [[South Ossetia]]) are shown in pink.]]\n[[File:Samtskhe-Javakheti in Georgia.svg|250px|right|thumb|Location of Samtskhe\u2013Javakheti within Georgia]]\n\n;Breakaway states\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Abkhazia.svg}} [[Abkhazia]]\n* People: [[Abkhaz people|Abkhaz]]\n** De facto state with [[International recognition of Abkhazia and South Ossetia|partial de jure recognition]]: {{flag|Republic of Abkhazia}}\n** Political organisation: [[Government of Abkhazia]]\n** Militant organization: [[Abkhazia Army|Abkhazian Armed Forces