ent]], [[Kuban Cossack Youth]], [[New Kuban Cossack Association]], [[Southern Regional Resource Center]], [[Union of Cossack Republics of Southern Russia]]\n***Militant organization: [[Kuban Cossack Army]]\n***Political parties: [[Free Cossack Movement]], [[Lapin]], [[Movement for the Federalizations of Kuban]], [[Union of the Cossack Hosts of Russia]], [[Union of the Cossack Hosts of Russia and Abroad]], [[Committee for the Liberation of the Kuban]]\n***Political organizations: [[Cossack Congress]], [[Cossacks of the Kuban Rada]]\n**Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Flag of Kuban People's Republic.svg}} [[Kuban People's Republic]] (proclaimed in 1918), [[Kuban Republic]] (attempted to proclaim in 1991 as part of [[Union of Cossack Republics in Southern Russia]] in [[Union of Sovereign States]] that never founded both) Currently asking for federalisation (Now consist of [[Krasnodar Krai]] and accommodates the republics of [[Republic of Adygea|Adygea]], [[Karachay-Cherkessia]], and parts of [[Stavropol Krai]]).\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Don Cossacks.svg}} [[Don Republic]]<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/05/world/europe/cossacks-face-reprisals-as-rebel-groups-clash-in-eastern-ukraine.html</ref><ref>https://www.refworld.org/docid/51dfba394.html</ref>\n*People: [[Don Cossacks]]\n**Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Flag of Don Cossacks.svg}} [[Don Republic]] / [[Rostov Oblast]]\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Kalmykia.svg}} [[Kalmykia]] <ref>https://jamestown.org/kalmyks-protest-donbas-separatist-who-was-appointed-mayor-of-republican-capital/</ref> <ref>https://www.refworld.org/docid/49749cbf2.html</ref>\n*People: [[Kalmyk people]]\n**Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Flag of Kalmykia.svg}} [[Kalmykia]]\n\n===North Caucasian Federal District===\n{{main|Insurgency in the North Caucasus|Caucasus Emirate|Mountainous Republic of the Northern Caucasus|Ajnad al-Kavkaz|Russification}}\n[[File:Russian Caucasus separatist movement and proposal state (2).jpg|250px|thumb|Right|A map of list federal subjects and districts that has separatist movements in North Caucasus Federal District.]]\n[[File:Chechnya and Caucasus.png|thumb|right|250px|Map of the North Caucasus region]]\n\n{{Flag|Chechnya}}\n*People: [[Chechens]]\n**Militant organisation: [[Chechen Republic of Ichkeria|Chechen separatists]]\n** Proposed state: {{flagicon|Chechen Republic of Ichkeria}} [[Chechen Republic of Ichkeria]] (government in exile)<ref>[http://www.frontpagemag.com/Articles/Read.aspx?GUID=17424AFF-8E69-4DE2-AE6E-C84B31DC2240 The Putin-Osama Connection]  {{webarchive|url=https://swap.stanford.edu/20090618192203/http://www.frontpagemag.com/Articles/Read.aspx?GUID=17424AFF-8E69-4DE2-AE6E-C84B31DC2240 |date=18 June 2009 }}, [[Frontpage Magazine]], 16 January 2008</ref><ref>Sengupta and Chatterjee. [https://books.google.com/books?id=HUS6DQAAQBAJ&pg=PT116&lpg=PT116&dq=Ichkeria+government+in+exile&source=bl&ots=M5vUMl8jav&sig=MeI22JkvAQXxtOWkyiPZXUTNygc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiUrLvwlb7UAhWl6oMKHepEBkEQ6AEIUTAI#v=onepage&q=Ichkeria%20government%20in%20exile&f=false|Globalizing Geographies: Perspectives from Eurasia]. 15 December 2014. (page number not shown on page, but is available by text search): \"The Chechen Republic of Ichkeria has collapsed and since then only remains a government in exile\"</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2017/jun/06/facebook-chechnya-political-activist-page-deleted|title=Facebook blocks Chechnya activist page in latest case of wrongful censorship|work=[[The Guardian]]|author=Julia Wong|date=6 June 2017}} quote = \"The group is supportive of the Chechen Republic of Ichkeria, an unrecognized government consisting of exiled leaders from the wars for independence.\"</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/chechnya-national-guard-attack-facts-questioned/28531874.html|title=Facts In Attack On National Guard In Chechnya Questioned|date=6 June 2017|author=Liz Fuller|work=RFERL}} quote= \"Akhmed Zakayev, the head of t