ks of Serbia]]\n* Proposed autonomous province: {{flagicon image|Bosniak National Flag in Sandzak.svg}} [[Sand\u017eak]] \n* Advocacy groups (autonomist): [[List for Sand\u017eak]], [[Party of Democratic Action of Sand\u017eak]], [[Islamic Community in Serbia]]<ref name=\"novosti\">{{cite web|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/aktuelno.69.html:331099-Zukorlic-Autonomija-Sandzaka-sve-izvesnija|title=Zukorli\u0107: Autonomija Sand\u017eaka sve izvesnija|website=www.novosti.rs}}</ref>\n\n;Breakaway state\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Serbia (1992-2004).svg}} [[Autonomous Province of Kosovo and Metohija]]\n* People: [[Albanians in Kosovo]]\n* Proposed: {{flagicon|Kosovo}} [[Republic of Kosovo]], Unification with {{flag|Albania}}\n** ''De facto'' state: {{flagicon|Kosovo}} [[Kosovo|Republic of Kosovo]] ([[International recognition of Kosovo|recognised by 50% of UN member states]])\n*** Political organisation: [[Government of Kosovo]]\n*** Movement: [[Albanian nationalism in Kosovo]]\n\n==Slovakia==\n{{Main|Secession in Slovakia}}\n\n[[File:Slovakia 2011 Language.png|thumb|150px|Linguistic makeup of Slovakia, according to Census 2011]]\n\n;Autonomist movements\n\nSouthern Slovakia:\n* People: [[Hungarians in Slovakia|Hungarians]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: Territorial autonomy for the compact Hungarian ethnic block and cultural autonomy for the regions of Hungarian presence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bumm.sk/archivum/2013/07/20/84738_berenyi-a-tombnek-teruleti-a-szorvanynak-kulturalis-autonomiat |title=Ber\u00e9nyi: A t\u00f6mbnek ter\u00fcleti, a sz\u00f3rv\u00e1nynak kultur\u00e1lis auton\u00f3mi\u00e1t |publisher=bumm.sk |date=20 July 2013 |accessdate=29 March 2014}}</ref>\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Party of the Hungarian Community]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politics.hu/20130417/head-of-party-for-ethnic-hungarians-in-slovakia-says-autonomy-necessary-for-minoritys-survival/ |title=Head of party for ethnic Hungarians in Slovakia says autonomy necessary for minority's survival |publisher=politics.hu |date=17 April 2013 |accessdate=3 April 2014}}</ref> In 2010, the party renewed their demand for autonomy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mkp.sk/cikkek/2013/04/16/felvideki-onrendelkezes-kilatasairol-autonomia-albizottsag-ulesen |title=A felvid\u00e9ki \u00f6nrendelkez\u00e9s kil\u00e1t\u00e1sair\u00f3l az auton\u00f3mia albizotts\u00e1g \u00fcl\u00e9s\u00e9n |publisher=mkp.sk |date=16 April 2013 |accessdate=29 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330004540/http://www.mkp.sk/cikkek/2013/04/16/felvideki-onrendelkezes-kilatasairol-autonomia-albizottsag-ulesen |archivedate=30 March 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Spain==\n{{Further|National and regional identity in Spain}}\n{{See also|List of active separatist movements in Africa#Spain}}\n[[File:Separatismos na Espanha.svg|thumb|300px|Regions in Spain with autonomist or separatist movements]]\n[[File:Aragon in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Aragon]]]]\n[[File:Asturias in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Asturias]]]]\n[[File:Islas Baleares in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Islas Baleares]]]]\n[[File:Islas Canarias (real location) in Spain.svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Islas Canarias]]]]\n[[File:Galicia in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Galicia]]]]\n[[File:Navarra in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Navarra]]]]\n[[File:Comunidad Valenciana in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Valenciana]]]]\n[[File:Cataluna in Spain (plus Canarias).svg|thumb|right|300px|[[Cataluna]]]]\n\n;Secessionist movements\n\n{{Flag|Andalusia}}\n{{Main|Andalusian nationalism}}\n* People: [[Andalusian people|Andalusian]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon|Andalusia}} [[Andalusian State|Andalusia]]\n*** Political parties (nationalist): [[Bloque Andaluz de Izquierdas]], [[Partido Comunista del Pueblo Andaluz]]\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[Naci\u00f3n Andaluza]], [[Asamblea Nacional de Andaluc\u00eda]], [[Candidatura Unitaria de Trabajadores]]\n*** Youth movements: [[Jaleo!!!]], [[Juventud Independentista Revolucionaria Andaluza]], [[Andalucista Youth|Juventudes Andalucistas]]\n*** Trade union: [[Sindicato Andaluz de Trabajadores]]\n\n{{Flag|Aragon}}\n{{Main|Aragonese nationalism}}\n* People: [[Aragonese people|Aragonese]]\n** Proposed state\n*** Socialist<!-- soveranists and separatists-->:  {{Flagicon image|EstreladaAragonesa.svg}} [[Regional Defence Council of Aragon|Aragon]]\n*** Federalist<!-- soveranists -->: {{Flagicon|Aragon}} [[Aragonese State|Aragon]]\n**** Political party (nationalist): [[Aragonese Council|Chunta Aragonesista]] (EFA member), [[Tierra Aragonesa]]\n**** Political party (secessionist): [[Aragonese State (political party)|Estau Aragon\u00e9s]], [http://www.puyalon.org/ Puyal\u00f3n de Cuchas], \n**** Youth movements: [[Purna Astral]], [[Chobenalla Aragonesista]]\n**** Trade union: [http://www.nazionobrera.blogspot.com/ Sindicato Obrero Aragon\u00e9s] (SOA)\n**** Other pro-independence organisations: A Enrestida, [[Sindicato d'Estudiants Independentistas y Revolucionarias d'Arag\u00f3n]] ([https://twitter.com/seiraragon/ SEIRA]), [[Bloque Independentista de Cuchas]]\n\n{{Flag|Asturias}}\n{{Main|Asturian nationalism}}\n* People: [[Asturian people|Asturians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon|Asturias}} [[Asturian State|Asturias]]\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Part\u00edu Asturianista]], [[Asturian Renewal Union|Uni\u00f3n Renovadora Asturiana]]\n*** Political parties (nationalist): [[Unid\u00e1 Nacionalista Asturiana]] (EFA member), [[Unid\u00e1]], [[Bloque por Asturies]], [[Compromisu por Asturies]]\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[Andecha Astur]]\n*** Youth movements: [[Darr\u00e9u]], [[UNA-Moced\u00e1]], [[Fai!]]\n*** Trade unions: [[Corriente Sindical d'Izquierda]], [[SUATEA]]\n*** Other pro-independence organisations: [[Sofitu]]\n\n{{Flag|Balearic Islands}}\n{{Main|Catalan nationalism}}\n* People: Balearics \u2013 [[Catalan people|Catalanics]] (those with Catalan ancestry)\n** Proposed state: {{Flag icon|Balearic Islands}} [[State of the Balearic Islands|Balearic Islands]] \u2013 {{Flagicon image|Si\u00f1al d'Arag\u00f3n.svg}} [[Catalan Countries]] (Confederation of Catalan States)\n*** Political parties: [[Majorca Socialist Party|Partit Socialista de Mallorca-Entesa Nacionalista]] (in [[Majorca]]), [[M\u00e9s per Menorca]], [[M\u00e9s per Mallorca]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Arran (organization)|Arran]], [[Joventuts d'Esquerra Republicana de les Illes Balears]]\n\n{{Flagicon|Basque Country}} [[Basque Country (autonomous community)]]\n{{Main|Basque nationalism|Basque independence}}\n* People: [[Basque people|Basques]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon|Basque Country}} [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country (greater region) \u2013 ''Euskal Herria'']]<ref name=\"academia.edu\"/>\n*** Political parties: [[Basque Nationalist Party|Euzko Alderdi Jeltzalea]] (Basque Nationalist Party) (member of the [[European Democratic Party]]), [[Eusko Alkartasuna]] (EFA member), [[Bildu]], [[Eusko Abertzale Ekintza]] (Basque Nationalist Action)\n*** Trade union: [[Euskal Langileen Alkartasuna]], [[Langile Abertzaleen Batzordeak]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Euzko Gaztedi|EGI]], [[Gazte Abertzaleak]], [[Haika]] (''illegalised'') [[Segi (organization)|Segi]], [[Ikasle Abertzaleak]]\n<!-- Former pro-independence organisations: [[Koordinadora Abertzale Sozialista]], [[Gestores Pro Amnist\u00eda]], [[Abertzale Sozialista Komiteak]], [[Egizan]] -->\n\n{{Flag|Canary Islands}}\n{{Main|Canarian nationalism}}\n* People: [[Canarian people|Canarians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Bandera Siete Estrellas Verdes.svg}} [[Canary Islands|Republic of the Canary Islands]]\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Coalici\u00f3n Canaria]], [[Partido Nacionalista Canario]], [[Centro Canario Nacionalista]], [[Nueva Canarias]]\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[FREPIC-AWA\u00d1AK]], [[Alter