es: [[Geroa Bai]], [[Bildu]], [[Basque Nationalist Action]], [[Batasuna]]\n*** Militant organisations: [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] (''Euskadi Ta Askatasuna'') (ceasefire since 2011)\n\n{{Flagicon|Valencian Community}} [[Valencian Community|Valencia]]\n{{Main|Valencianism|Valencian nationalism|Catalan nationalism}}\n* People: [[Valencian people|Valencians]] \u2013 [[Catalan people|Catalanics]] (those with Catalan ancestry)\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Senyera del nacionalisme valenci\u00e0.svg}} [[Valencian State|Valencian Country]] or unification with {{Flagicon image|Si\u00f1al d'Arag\u00f3n.svg}} [[Catalan Countries]]\n*** Political parties: [[Valencian Nationalist Bloc]], [[Initiative of the Valencian People]], [[Popular Unity Candidates]], [[Republican Left of the Valencian Country]], [[Valencian State (political party)|Valencian State]], [[Valencian Nationalist Left]], [[Valencian Left]]\n*** Advocacy groups: Pro-Catalan Valencianists (who defend [[pan-Catalanism]] and [[Fusterianism|Fuster's theories]]) propose the creation of a Valencian State and some type of reconnection with the rest of Catalan-speaking areas. Only a minor tendency within anti-Catalan Valencianism ([[Blaverism]]) proposed independence of the Kingdom of Valencia from both Catalonia and Spain.<ref>[http://independenciavalenciana.blogspot.com Independ\u00e8ncia Valenciana] (Valencian)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenciafreedom.com/es/noticias/inicio.html|title=Noticias - Valenciafreedom - La web que lucha contra la imposicion catalanista|website=www.valenciafreedom.com}}</ref>\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Arran (organization)|Arran]], Youths of Comprom\u00eds (mostly soveranist and non-secessionist), Youths of Republican Left of the Valencian Country\n*** Trade union: [[Intersindical Valenciana]]\n*** Other organisations: [[Valencian Sovereignty]] (''Sobirania Valenciana'')\n\nAdditionally, there are a number of almost extinct secessionist or soveranist movements in other autonomous communities and historical territories, e.g. [[Extremadura]] and [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]].\n\n{{Flagicon image|Flag-Val d' Aran.svg}} [[Val d'Aran|Aran Valley]]\n{{Main|Aranese nationalism|Occitan nationalism}}\n* People: Aranese (a subset of Gascon Occitans)\n** Proposed autonomous area: [[Val d'Aran|Aran Valley]] \u2013 within {{Flag|Catalonia}} or Unification with {{Flag|Occitania}}\n*** Political parties: [[Aranese Democratic Convergence|Converg\u00e8ncia Democr\u00e0tica Aranesa]], [[Unitat d'Aran]], [[Partit Renovador d'Arties-Gar\u00f2s]], [[Esqu\u00e8rra Republicana Occitana]], [[Partit de la Nacion Occitana]], [[Partit Occitan]]\n\n==Switzerland==\n{{Main|Secession in Switzerland}}\n{{Main|Languages of Switzerland}}\n[[File:FRP-Map4.png|thumb|150px|right|Jura region]]\n[[File:Map Languages CH.png|thumb|150px|left|The French-speaking part of Switzerland is shown in green on this map.]]\n\n;Autonomist movements\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Canton of Jura.svg}} Jura region\n{{see also|Jurassic separatism}}\n* People: [[Jurassien]] (French-speaking) \n** Proposed autonomous area: Unification of the three districts of [[Bernese Jura]] and the [[Laufen District]] with the {{flagicon image|Flag of Canton of Jura.svg}} [[Canton of Jura]]\n*** Militant organisations: [[Mouvement Autonomiste Jurassien]] (Jurassian Autonomist Movement),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maj.ch/mouvements |title=Mouvement autonomiste jurassien |trans-title=Jura autonomist movement |language=fr |publisher=Maj.ch |date= |accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref> [[Groupe B\u00e9lier]] (Youth activists movement)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.groupebelier.ch/|title=Groupe B\u00e9lier \u2013 Mouvement de lutte pour l'Unit\u00e9 du Jura|trans-title=Aries Group \u2013 Movement struggling for Jura Unity|language=fr|publisher=Groupebelier.ch |date=14 March 2015|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Turkey ==\n[[File:EstThraceWithinThrace.png|thumbnail|150px|[[East Thrace]] (blue) within [[Thrace]]]]\n\n{{Main|Secession in Turkey}}\n{{See also|Minorities in Turkey}}\n{{Further|1934 Thrace pogroms|Greek genocide|Turkish nationalism|Turkish War of Independence|Treaty of S\u00e8vres|Treaty of Lausanne}}\n\n{{hatnote|No known movements in the geographic European side of Turkey ([[East Thrace]]), for the movements in the rest of Turkey, see [[List of active separatist movements in Asia#Turkey|List of active separatist movements in Asia \u00a7 Turkey]]}}\n\n==Ukraine==\n{{Main|Secession in Ukraine}}\n[[File:2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine.png|thumb|150px|right|A map of the [[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine|2014 pro-Russian protests and unrest in Ukraine]], by oblast. Severity of the unrest, at its peak, is indicated by the colouring. 'RSA' indicates 'Regional State Administration', the name for the governments of the oblasts (regions) of Ukraine.]]\n[[File:Map of the war in Donbass.svg|thumb|150px|Occupied territories of [[Eastern Ukraine]], controlled by [[Donetsk People's Republic|DPR]] and [[Luhansk People's Republic|LPR]]]]\n\n;Breakaway states\n\n{{flagicon|Crimea}} [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea]]\n* People: [[Crimeans]], [[Russians in Crimea|Russians]]\n* Proposed: {{flagicon|Crimea}} [[Republic of Crimea]] (within the {{flagicon|Russia}} [[Russian Federation]])\n** ''De facto'' state: {{flagicon|Crimea}} [[Republic of Crimea]] ''(see: [[Political status of Crimea]])''\n*** Political organisation: [[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine|Pro-Russian separatists]], [[Russian government]]\n*** Movement: [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation]]\n\n;De facto states\n\n{{flag|Luhansk Oblast}} ([[Luhansk People's Republic|occupied areas]])\n* People: [[Russians in Ukraine]]\n* Proposed: {{flag|Luhansk People's Republic}}\n** De facto state: {{flag|Luhansk People's Republic}}\n*** Political parties: [[Free Donbass]], [[New Russia Party]]\n*** Militant organization: [[United Armed Forces of Novorossiya|Luhansk People's Militia]]\n\n{{flag|Donetsk Oblast}} ([[Donetsk People's Republic|occupied areas]])\n* People: [[Russians in Ukraine]]\n* Proposed: {{flag|Donetsk People's Republic}}\n** De facto state: {{flag|Donetsk People's Republic}}\n*** Political organisation: [[People's Soviet of the Donetsk People's Republic]]\n*** Political parties: [[Donetsk Republic (organization)|Donetsk Republic]], [[Free Donbass]], [[New Russia Party]]\n*** Militant organization: [[United Armed Forces of Novorossiya|Donbass People's Militia]]\n\n==United Kingdom==\n{{Main|Separatism in the United Kingdom|Federalism in the United Kingdom|Countries of the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[File:Uk-countries-labeled.gif|thumb|150px|Countries of the United Kingdom]]\n[[File:Map of the administrative geography of the United Kingdom.png|thumb|150px|Map of current local administrative units in the United Kingdom]]\n[[File:Cornwall UK locator map 2010.svg|thumb|150px|right|[[Cornwall]]]] \n[[File:England 878.svg|thumb|150px|[[Wessex]] - England in the late 9th century|alt=Map of England in the late ninth century]]\n[[File:North East England in England.svg|thumb|150px|[[North East England]]]]\n[[File:Yorkshire UK 1851 locator map.svg|thumb|150px|[[Yorkshire]]]]\n[[File:Kingdom of Mann and the Isles-en.svg|thumb|right|150px|The [[Kingdom of the Isles]] about the year 1100]]\n[[File:Europe-Isle of Man.svg|thumb|right|150px|[[Isle of Man]]]]\n\n;Secessionist movements\n\n{{flag|Cornwall}}\n{{See also|Cornish nationalism}}\n* People: [[Cornish people|Cornish]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Cornwall}}\n*** Political parties: [[Mebyon Kernow]]\n***Advocacy groups: [[Celtic League]]<ref name=celticleague>{{cite web|url=https://www.celticleague.net/current-campaigns/|title=Current Campaigns|publisher=[[Celtic League]]|accessdate=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{flag|England}}\n{{See also|English nationalism|English independence}}\n* People: [[English people|English]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|England}}\n*** Political parties: [[English Democrats]]<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"