t location.svg|thumb|left|100px|Location of the Banat (dark green)]]\n[[File:Transylvania, Banat, Crisana and Maramures.svg|thumb|left|100px|[[Transylvania]]]]\n\n[[Hungarians in Romania|Hungarian community in Romania]]\n* People: [[Hungarians in Romania|Hungarians]] and [[Sz\u00e9kelys]]\n** Proposals for Hungarian territorial autonomy:\n*** {{Flagicon image|Szekely.gif}} [[Sz\u00e9kely Land]]: [[Sz\u00e9kely autonomy initiatives]]\n*** {{Flagicon image|Flag of Partium.svg}} [[Partium]]\n** Political organisations: [[Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania]], the demand for Hungarian autonomy has been part of their program since 1993.<ref>{{cite web|trans-title=Barber's autonomy from the draft: ahem, that scared! | url= http://www.kronika.ro/erdelyi-hirek/borbely-az-autonomiatervezetrol-ejnye-hogy-megijedtunk | title =Borb\u00e9ly az auton\u00f3miatervezet r\u0151l: ejnye, hogy megijedt\u00fcnk! |publisher= kronika | language = ro |date= 28 March 2014 |accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref> [[Hungarian Civic Party (Romania)|Hungarian Civic Party]], they signed a settlement with the Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania about cooperation and joint support for Hungarian autonomy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://itthon.transindex.ro/?hir=35851 |title=J\u00f6v\u0151 h\u00e9ten egyeztet az MPP \u00e9s az RMDSZ az auton\u00f3mia-tervezetr\u0151l|publisher=transindex.ro |date=25 March 2014 |accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref> [[Hungarian People's Party of Transylvania]] (PPMT), the party proposes the establishments of Transylvanian parliament and government and supports the case of Szekler autonomy in Szekely Land.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.nationalia.info/en/news/1255 |title=Cultural autonomy and territorial federalism: two voting options for Hungarians in Transylvania|publisher= Nationalia |date=13 November 2012 |accessdate=28 May 2014}}</ref> It also advocates territorial autonomy for [[Partium]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://kitekinto.hu/karpat-medence/2013/07/22/megalakult_a_partiumi_autonomia_tanacs/ |title = Megalakult a Partiumi Auton\u00f3mia Tan\u00e1cs |trans-title=The formation of the Partium Council Autonomy | publisher= Kitekinto | language = hu |date=22 July 2013 | accessdate = 20 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | trans-title = Open tender for the design of the Partium symbols | url = http://erdely.ma/palyazatok.php?id=165220&cim=nyilt_palyazat_a_partium_jelkepeinek_megtervezesere | title = Ny\u00edlt p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat a Partium jelk\u00e9peinek megtervez\u00e9s\u00e9re | publisher = Erdely | language = hu | date = 21 May 2013 | accessdate = 20 June 2014 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140701110414/http://erdely.ma/palyazatok.php?id=165220&cim=nyilt_palyazat_a_partium_jelkepeinek_megtervezesere | archivedate = 1 July 2014 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n** Advocacy organisations: [[Szekler National Council]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://sznt.sic.hu/en/ |title = Szekler National Council | place = [[Transilvania]] |accessdate = 12 April 2009}}</ref> [[Hungarian National Council of Transylvania]], [[Liga Pro Europa]], a Romanian-Hungarian [[Regionalism (politics)|regionalist]] NGO,<ref name='Filep'>{{cite web|url= http://www.etd.ceu.hu/2007/filep_bela.pdf |title= Cooperating regionalist and autonomy movements in Europe | publisher = Central European University | year = 2007 | accessdate= 30 March 2014}}</ref> [[Provincia (Romania)|Provincia]], a group of intellectuals promoting regionalization of Romania.<ref name='Filep'/>\n\n;Other administrative proposals by regionalist organisations:\n\n* [[Banat]]<ref name=\"ligabanat\">{{cite web| url = http://www.ligabanateana.ro/program.htm| title = Program | publisher = Liga Banateana | language = ro | accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Transylvania]]<ref name=\"ligatran\">{{cite web|url = http://www.neuerweg.ro/de-ce-liga-transilvania-democrata/ |title= De ce \"Liga Transilvania Democrat\u0103\" |trans-title=Why \"Transylvania Democratic League\" | publisher= Neuerweg | language = ro |date=21 March 2014 | accessdate = 15 June 2014}}</ref>\n** Political organisations: [[Liga Transilvania-Banat]], a regionalist party led by Sabin Gherman.<ref name='Filep'/>\n** Advocacy organisations: [[Autonomy for Transylvania]] (AFT) campaign, it demands autonomy for Transylvania.<ref>{{cite web |trans-title=Petition for the autonomy of Transylvania, Cluj filed Prefecture | url = http://www.romanialibera.ro/actualitate/proiecte-locale/petitie-pentru-autonomia-transilvaniei--depusa-la-prefectura-cluj-328819 |title = Peti\u0163ie pentru autonomia Transilvaniei, depus\u0103 la Prefectura Cluj| publisher = Romania libera | language = ro | date = 12 March 2014 | accessdate=30 March 2014}}</ref> [[Democratic League of Transylvania]] (Liga Transilvania Democrat\u0103), a regionalist NGO,<ref name=\"ligatran\"/> an active supporter of the \"Autonomy for Transylvania\" campaign,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://novatv.ro/2013/10/candidat-la-europarlamentare-in-lupta-pentru-autonomia-transilvaniei-dam-un-semnal-clar-pentru-politicienii-din-romania-si-ue/ |title=Liga Transilvania Democrat\u0103 a mai anun\u0163at c\u0103 se va implica \u015fi din punct de vedere logistic pentru a ob\u0163ine num\u0103rul necesar de semn\u0103turi |trans-title=Transylvania Democratic League announced that it will involve and logistically to get the required number of signatures | publisher = Nova TV | language = ro |date=15 October 2013 |accessdate=15 June 2014}}</ref> [[League of Banat]] (Liga Banateana), a regionalist NGO.<ref name=\"ligabanat\"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://adevarul.ro/locale/timisoara/banatenii-vor-autonomie-economica-administrativa-acest-lucru-nu-inseamna-independenta-ruperea-romania-1_50ae7e167c42d5a6639d3941/index.html |trans-title=Economic and administrative autonomy of Banat: \"This does not mean independence or breaking of Romania\" | title=B\u0103n\u0103\u0163enii vor autonomie economic\u0103 \u015fi administrativ\u0103: \"Acest lucru nu \u00eenseamn\u0103 independen\u0163a sau ruperea de Rom\u00e2nia\" | publisher= Adevarul | language = ro |date=29 October 2012 |accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref> Also, from 2015 another group advocating for the reunification and independence of the Banat started to merge, under the leadership of the titular Duke Clovis-William I of Stepanescu-Vlaicu, the current head of House Vlaicu from the Osli-Csornay clan, and a direct descendant of House Csan\u00e1d via female line. This group, with no political organisation yet, advocates for clan and peerage revival, complete independence or condominium, conservative nationalism, the constitution of an Intermarium Commonwealth under the symbolic rulership of House Habsburg-Lothringen, and euroscepticism.\n\n==Russia==\n{{Main|Dissolution of Russia}}\n{{See also|List of active separatist movements in Asia#Russia}}\n\n===Summary===\nThis table shows only the list of movements. The source of each movement is cited in its own section. The population of each area is provided for information only.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%\"\n|-\n!width=75|Number\n!width=250|Land\n!width=125|Capital\n!width=100|Area\n!width=100|Population\n!width=125|Ethnic\n!width=300|Main Political Party\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"#9acdff\" align=\"center\" |'''[[Ural Federal District]] of [[European Russia]]'''\n|-\n| align=center|1 || '''[[File:Flag of Sverdlovsk Oblast.svg|23px|border]] [[Ural Republic]]''' || '''[[Yekaterinburg]]''' || align=center|194,800 || align=center|4,300,000 || [[Russian people]] || Ural Democratic Foundation\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"#9acdff\" align=\"center\" |'''[[Volga Federal District]] of [[European Russia]]'''\n|-\n| align=center|2 || '''[[File:Flag of Idel-Ural State.svg|23px|border]] [[Idel-Ural State|Idel-Ural]]''' || '''[[Kazan]]''' || align=center|321,400 || align=center|11,000,000 || [[Volga region|Volga people]] || [[Free Idel-Ural]]\n|-\n| align=center|3 || '''[[File:Flag of Bashkortosta