RA]), [[Bloque Independentista de Cuchas]]\n\n{{Flag|Asturias}}\n{{Main|Asturian nationalism}}\n* People: [[Asturian people|Asturians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon|Asturias}} [[Asturian State|Asturias]]\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Part\u00edu Asturianista]], [[Asturian Renewal Union|Uni\u00f3n Renovadora Asturiana]]\n*** Political parties (nationalist): [[Unid\u00e1 Nacionalista Asturiana]] (EFA member), [[Unid\u00e1]], [[Bloque por Asturies]], [[Compromisu por Asturies]]\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[Andecha Astur]]\n*** Youth movements: [[Darr\u00e9u]], [[UNA-Moced\u00e1]], [[Fai!]]\n*** Trade unions: [[Corriente Sindical d'Izquierda]], [[SUATEA]]\n*** Other pro-independence organisations: [[Sofitu]]\n\n{{Flag|Balearic Islands}}\n{{Main|Catalan nationalism}}\n* People: Balearics \u2013 [[Catalan people|Catalanics]] (those with Catalan ancestry)\n** Proposed state: {{Flag icon|Balearic Islands}} [[State of the Balearic Islands|Balearic Islands]] \u2013 {{Flagicon image|Si\u00f1al d'Arag\u00f3n.svg}} [[Catalan Countries]] (Confederation of Catalan States)\n*** Political parties: [[Majorca Socialist Party|Partit Socialista de Mallorca-Entesa Nacionalista]] (in [[Majorca]]), [[M\u00e9s per Menorca]], [[M\u00e9s per Mallorca]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Arran (organization)|Arran]], [[Joventuts d'Esquerra Republicana de les Illes Balears]]\n\n{{Flagicon|Basque Country}} [[Basque Country (autonomous community)]]\n{{Main|Basque nationalism|Basque independence}}\n* People: [[Basque people|Basques]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon|Basque Country}} [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country (greater region) \u2013 ''Euskal Herria'']]<ref name=\"academia.edu\"/>\n*** Political parties: [[Basque Nationalist Party|Euzko Alderdi Jeltzalea]] (Basque Nationalist Party) (member of the [[European Democratic Party]]), [[Eusko Alkartasuna]] (EFA member), [[Bildu]], [[Eusko Abertzale Ekintza]] (Basque Nationalist Action)\n*** Trade union: [[Euskal Langileen Alkartasuna]], [[Langile Abertzaleen Batzordeak]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Euzko Gaztedi|EGI]], [[Gazte Abertzaleak]], [[Haika]] (''illegalised'') [[Segi (organization)|Segi]], [[Ikasle Abertzaleak]]\n<!-- Former pro-independence organisations: [[Koordinadora Abertzale Sozialista]], [[Gestores Pro Amnist\u00eda]], [[Abertzale Sozialista Komiteak]], [[Egizan]] -->\n\n{{Flag|Canary Islands}}\n{{Main|Canarian nationalism}}\n* People: [[Canarian people|Canarians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Bandera Siete Estrellas Verdes.svg}} [[Canary Islands|Republic of the Canary Islands]]\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Coalici\u00f3n Canaria]], [[Partido Nacionalista Canario]], [[Centro Canario Nacionalista]], [[Nueva Canarias]]\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[FREPIC-AWA\u00d1AK]], [[Alternativa Nacionalista Canaria]], [[Alternativa Popular Canaria]], [[Unidad del Pueblo]]\n***Trade union: [[Intersindical Canaria]]\n*** Youth movement: [[Azarug]]\n\n{{Flagicon image|Flag of Castile.svg}} [[Castile (historical region)|Castile]]\n{{Main|Castilian nationalism}}\n* People [[Castilian people|Castilians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Flag of Castile.svg}} [[Castile (state)|Castile]]\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Partido Castellano]] PCas\n*** Political parties (secessionist): [[Izquierda Castellana]]\n*** Youth movements: [[Yesca]]\n\n{{Flag|Catalonia}}\n{{Main|Catalan nationalism|Catalan independence|Catalan independence referendum, 2017|Catalan declaration of independence}}\n* People: [[Catalan people|Catalans]]\n** Proposal state: {{Flagicon|Catalonia}} [[Catalan Republic (2017)|Catalan Republic]] \u2013 {{Flagicon image|Si\u00f1al d'Arag\u00f3n.svg}} [[Pa\u00efsos Catalans|Catalan Countries]] (Confederation of Catalan States) (i.e. including other Catalan-speaking areas)\n*** Political parties:\n**** [[Junts per Catalunya|JuntsxCat]] (34/135), [[Republican Left of Catalonia\u2013Catalonia Yes]] (32/135): coalition to stand in the [[2017 Catalan parliamentary election]] supported by [[Republican Left of Catalonia]] (33/135 seats in the Catalan parliament) and [[Democrats of Catalonia]] (3/135), [[Left Movement]] (1/135) and other small parties and civil organisations\n**** [[Popular Unity Candidacy\u2013Constituent Call]], coalition to stand in the [[2015 Catalan parliamentary election]] supported by [[Popular Unity Candidacy]] (4/135) and other small parties and civil organisations\n*** Political parties (autonomist): [[Catalunya en Com\u00fa\u2013Podem]] (8/135)\n*** Civil organisations: [[Assemblea Nacional Catalana]], [[\u00d2mnium Cultural]], [[Association of Municipalities for Independence]], Proc\u00e9s Constituent, Catalunya Acci\u00f3, Sobirania i Progr\u00e9s, [[Committees for the Defense of the Republic]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Arran (organization)|Arran]], [[La Forja]], [[Joventuts d'Esquerra Republicana de Catalunya]], ''Joves d'Esquerra Verda'', ''Joventut Nacionalista de Catalunya'', ''Uni\u00f3 de Joves''\n\n{{Flagicon|Galicia}} [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]]\n{{Main|Galicianism|Galician nationalism|Galician independence}}\n* People: [[Galician people|Galicians]]\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Bandeira galega civil.svg}} [[Galician State]]\n*** Political party: [[Bloque Nacionalista Galego]] (Galician Nationalist Block) (autonomist) (EFA member), [[Frente Popular Galego]] ([[Galician Popular Front]]) (independentist), [[Terra Galega]] Galician Coalition (Centrist nationalist Party), [[Galician Left Alternative|Alternativa Galega de Esquedas (Galician Left Alternative)]]\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Xeira]], Galiza Nova, AGIR, CAF\n*** Militant organisation: [[Resist\u00eancia Galega]]\n\n{{Flagicon image|Bandera del Pa\u00eds Leon\u00e9s.svg}} [[Le\u00f3n (historical region)|Le\u00f3n]]\n{{Main|Leonese regionalism}}\n* People: [[Leonese people|Leonese]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{Flagicon image|Bandera del Pa\u00eds Leon\u00e9s.svg}} [[Le\u00f3n (historical region)|Leonese region]]\n*** Political parties: [[Leonese People's Union|Uni\u00f3n del Pueblo Leon\u00e9s UPL]]\n*** Youth movements: RUCHAR Moced\u00e1 Llionesa<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mocedallionesa.blogspot.com.es/2016/04/presentacion-ruchar-moceda-llionesa.html|title=Ruchar Moced\u00e1 Llionesa: Presentaci\u00f3n RUCHAR Moced\u00e1 Llionesa|last=Llionesa|first=Ruchar Moced\u00e1|website=Ruchar Moced\u00e1 Llionesa|access-date=2016-09-09}}</ref>\n*** Advocacy groups: [[AGORA Pa\u00eds Llion\u00e9s]]\n*** Militant organisations: [[Tierra Lleunesa]]\n\n{{Flag|Navarre}}\n{{Main|Basque nationalism}}\n* People: Navarran or Navarrese (a subgroup of [[Basque people]])\n** Proposed states: Unification with the {{Flag|Basque Country}} \u2013 ''[[Basque Country (greater region)|Euskal Herria]]''\n*** Political parties: [[Geroa Bai]], [[Bildu]], [[Basque Nationalist Action]], [[Batasuna]]\n*** Militant organisations: [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] (''Euskadi Ta Askatasuna'') (ceasefire since 2011)\n\n{{Flagicon|Valencian Community}} [[Valencian Community|Valencia]]\n{{Main|Valencianism|Valencian nationalism|Catalan nationalism}}\n* People: [[Valencian people|Valencians]] \u2013 [[Catalan people|Catalanics]] (those with Catalan ancestry)\n** Proposed state: {{Flagicon image|Senyera del nacionalisme valenci\u00e0.svg}} [[Valencian State|Valencian Country]] or unification with {{Flagicon image|Si\u00f1al d'Arag\u00f3n.svg}} [[Catalan Countries]]\n*** Political parties: [[Valencian Nationalist Bloc]], [[Initiative of the Valencian People]], [[Popular Unity Candidates]], [[Republican Left of the Valencian Country]], [[Valencian State (political party)|Valencian State]], [[Valencian Nationalist Left]], [[Valencian Left]]\n*** Advocacy groups: Pro-Catalan Valencianists (who defend [[pan-Catalanism]] and [[Fusterianism|Fuster's theories]]) propose the creation of a Valencian State and some type of reconnection with the rest of Catalan-speaking areas. Only a minor tendency within anti-Catalan Valencianism ([[Blaverism]]) proposed independence of the Kingdom of Valencia from both Catalonia and Spain.<ref>[http://independenciavalenciana.blogspot.com Independ\u00e8ncia Valenciana] (Valencian)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenciafreedom.com/es/noticias/inicio.html|title=Noticias - Valenciafreedom - La web que lucha contra la imposicion catalanista|website=www.valenciafreedom.com}}</ref>\n*** Youth advocacy groups: [[Arran (organization)|Arran]], Youths of Comprom\u00eds (mostly soveranist and non-secessionist), Youths of Republican Left of the Valencian Country\n*** Trade union: [[Intersindical Valenciana]]\n*** Other organisations: [[Valencian Sovereignty]] (''Sobirania Valenciana'')\n\nAdditionally, there are a number of almost extinct secessionist or soveranist movements in other autonomous communities and historical territories, e.g. [[Extremadura]] and [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]].\n\n{{Flagicon image|Flag-Val d' Aran.svg}} [[Val d'Aran|Aran Valley]]\n{{Main|Aranese nationalism|Occitan nationalism}}\n* People: Aranese (a subset of Gascon Occitans)\n** Proposed autonomous area: [[Val d'Aran|Aran Valley]] \u2013 within {{Flag|Catalonia}} or Unification with {{Flag|Occitania}}\n*** Political parties: [[Aranese Democratic Convergence|Converg\u00e8ncia Democr\u00e0tica Aranesa]], [[Unitat d'Aran]], [[Partit Renovador d'Arties-Gar\u00f2s]], [[Esqu\u00e8rra Republicana Occitana]], [[Partit de la Nacion Occitana]], [[Partit Occitan]]\n\n==Switzerland==\n{{Main|Secession in Switzerland}}\n{{Main|Languages of Switzerland}}\n[[File:FRP-Map4.png|thumb|150px|right|Jura region]]\n[[File:Map Languages CH.png|thumb|150px|left|The French-speaking part of Switzerland is shown in green on this map.]]\n\n;Autonomist movements\n\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Canton of Jura.svg}} Jura region\n{{see also|Jurassic separatism}}\n* People: [[Jurassien]] (French-speaking) \n** Proposed autonomous area: Unification of the three districts of [[Bernese Jura]] and the 