h Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament|Scottish CND]], [[Voices for Scotland|Voice for Scotland]], [[Women for Independence]]), [[Yes Scotland]]\n\n{{flag|Wales}}\n{{See also|Welsh nationalism|Welsh independence}}\n* People: [[Welsh people|Welsh]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Wales|name=Wales}}\n*** Political parties: [[Plaid Cymru]], [[Cymru Annibynnol]], [[Cymru Sovereign]], [[Gwlad Gwlad]], [[Welsh National Party]]\n*** Advocacy groups: [[Celtic League (political organisation)|Celtic League]],<ref name=celticleague/> [[YesCymru]]\n\n;Autonomist movements\n{{See also|Devolution in the United Kingdom}}\n\n{{flag|England}}\n{{See also|Devolved English parliament|English nationalism}}\n* People: [[English people|English]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|England}}\n*** Political parties: [[English Democrats]],<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/> [[United Kingdom Independence Party|UKIP]]<ref>{{Citation | chapter-url = http://www.ukip.org/content/ukip-policies/1447-restoring-britishness-ukip-policy | chapter = Section 5: Solutions \u2013 Economic, Legal and Political Measures | title = Restoring Britishness: UKIP Policy | publisher = UK Independence Party | accessdate = 6 April 2010 | archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/6223ByTCt?url=http://www.ukip.org/content/ukip-policies/1447-restoring-britishness-ukip-policy| archivedate = 28 September 2011}}</ref>\n*** Advocacy groups: [[Campaign for an English Parliament]]\n\n{{flag|Scotland}}\n{{See also|Devolution in Scotland|Scottish nationalism}}\n* People: [[Scottish people|Scots]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Scotland}}\n*** Political parties: [[Scottish National Party]] (EFA member)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jun/15/scottish-government-renews-call-extra-powers-tax-welfare|title=Scottish government renews call for extra powers on tax and welfare|work=The Guardian|date=16 June 2015|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{flag|Wales}}\n{{See also|Welsh nationalism}}\n* People: [[Welsh people|Welsh]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Wales}}\n*** Political parties: [[Plaid Cymru]]\n\n{{Flag|Cornwall}} (possibly including the [[Isles of Scilly]])\n{{See also|Cornish nationalism|Constitutional status of Cornwall|Cornish Assembly}}\n* People: [[Cornish people|Cornish]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Cornwall}}\n*** Political parties: [[Green Party of England and Wales]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Green Party will support calls for a Cornish Assembly|url=http://www.cornishguardian.co.uk/Green-Party-support-calls-Cornish-Assembly/story-21073305-detail/story.html|newspaper=The Cornish Guardian|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=8 May 2014}}</ref> [[Mebyon Kernow]] (EFA member), [[Cornish Nationalist Party]], [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Liberal Democrats vote for Cornish Assembly|author=Graeme Demianyk|url=http://www.westernmorningnews.co.uk/Liberal-Democrats-vote-Cornish-Assembly/story-20789336-detail/story.html|newspaper=The Western Morning News|date=10 March 2014|accessdate=6 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407090513/http://www.westernmorningnews.co.uk/Liberal-Democrats-vote-Cornish-Assembly/story-20789336-detail/story.html|archive-date=7 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"libdems-spring2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.libdems.org.uk/spring_conference_2014|title=Spring Conference 2014| publisher=Liberal Democrats|date=3 September 2014|accessdate=29 June 2015}}</ref>\n*** Advocacy groups: [[Celtic League (political organisation)|Celtic League]], [[Cornish Constitutional Convention]], [[Cornwall 2000]], [[Revived Cornish Stannary Parliament]], [[Wessex Constitutional Convention]]<ref>{{cite book| last1 = Robins| first1 = David | last2 = Xylas| first2 = Nick| title = The Case for Wessex| url = http://www.zyworld.com/wessexsociety/caseforwessex.pdf| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060220054322/http://www.zyworld.com/wessexsociety/caseforwessex.pdf| url-status = dead| archive-date = 20 February 2006| accessdate = 15 February 2013| date = 15 March 2003| publisher = Wessex Constitutional Convention| isbn = 978-0-9544667-0-1| page = 4}}</ref>\n\n\n[[North East England]]\n* People: [[Geordies]]\n* Proposed autonomous area: {{flagicon image|Flag of None.svg}} [[North East England]] or {{flagicon image|Flag of Northumbria.svg}} Northumbria<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lexico.com/en/definition/northumbria|title=Northumbria &#124; Definition of Northumbria in English by Lexico Dictionaries|website=Lexico Dictionaries &#124; English}}</ref>\n** Political parties: [[North East Party]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.co.uk/news/north-east-news/north-east-party-launches-7175897|title=North-east devolution? We could be like Plaid Cymru says new party's leader |accessdate=27 May 2014|ref=northeastparty}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon image|FlagOfWessex.svg}} [[Wessex#Cultural and political identity in modern times|Wessex]]<ref>{{cite book| last1 = Robins | first1 = David | last2 = Xylas | first2 = Nick | title = The Case for Wessex | url = http://www.zyworld.com/wessexsociety/caseforwessex.pdf | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060220054322/http://www.zyworld.com/wessexsociety/caseforwessex.pdf | url-status = dead | archive-date = 20 February 2006 | accessdate = 15 February 2013 | date = 15 March 2003 | publisher = Wessex Constitutional Convention| isbn = 978-0-9544667-0-1| page = 7}}</ref>\n* People: People of Wessex\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flagicon image|FlagOfWessex.svg}} [[Wessex#Cultural and political identity in modern times|Wessex]]\n*** Political parties: [[Wessex Regionalists]]\n*** Advocacy group: [[Wessex Constitutional Convention]]\n\n{{flag|Yorkshire}}\n* People: People of Yorkshire\n** Proposed autonomous area: {{flag|Yorkshire}}<ref>{{cite news|title=We want devolution, says York council leader|author=Mark Stead|url=http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/9610577.We_want_devolution__says_York_council_leader/|newspaper=The York Press|date=24 March 2012|accessdate=12 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yorkshireindependence.com/|title=The official website of the \"Yorkshire Independence \u2013 Campaign for devolution\"|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101206113608/http://www.yorkshireindependence.com/|archivedate=6 December 2010|date=22 November 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.facebook.com/pages/Yorkshire-Devolution-Movement/223743807767806 | title = The Yorkshire devolution movement | publisher = Facebook Account}}</ref><ref name=\"White Rose Parliament\">{{cite news|title= David Blunkett MP suggests \"Yorkshire Parliament\"|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-south-yorkshire-11637889 | accessdate =7 May 2014|publisher=BBC | work = News|date=27 October 2010}}</ref>\n*** Political parties: [[Yorkshire Party]]\n*** Advocacy group: Yorkshire Devolution Movement<ref>{{Citation | title = The Yorkshire devolution movement | url = https://yorkshiredevolutionmovementt.wordpress.com/ | publisher = Word press}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | url = http://yorkshiredevolution.co.uk/ | title = Yorkshire devolution}}</ref>\n\n;Independence movements of dependent territories\n{{flag|Isle of Man}}\n* People: [[Manx people|Manx]]\n* Proposed State: {{flag|Isle of Man}}\n** Political party: [[Mec Vannin]]\n** Advocacy group: [[Celtic League (political organisation)|Celtic League]]<ref name=celticleague/>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Europe|Politics}}\n* [[Lists of active separatist movements]]\n* [[List of historical separatist movements]]\n* [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]]\n* [[List of micro-regional organizations]]\n* [[List of states with limited recognition]]\n* [[Independence referendum]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Citation | contribution-url = http://www.alandsframtid.ax/images/Politiskaprogram/F%20valmanifest%202011.pdf | contribution = Manifest | year = 2011 | title = Politiskaprogram |trans-title=Political program |