i2015>{{cite book|last1=Miklosi|first1=Adam|title=Dog Behaviour, Evolution, and Cognition|publisher=Oxford University Press|edition=2|series=Oxford Biology|year=2015|pages=106\u2013107|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=VT-WBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA106|isbn=978-0199545667}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=morey2015>{{cite journal|doi=10.1016/j.jasrep.2015.06.031|title=Paleolithic dogs: Why sustained domestication then?|journal=Journal of Archaeological Science: Reports|volume=3|pages=420\u2013428|year=2015|last1=Morey|first1=Darcy F.|last2=Jeger|first2=Rujana}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=morey2016>{{cite journal|doi=10.1080/08912963.2016.1262854|title=From wolf to dog: Late Pleistocene ecological dynamics, altered trophic strategies, and shifting human perceptions|journal=Historical Biology|volume=29|issue=7|pages=1\u20139|year=2016|last1=Morey|first1=Darcy F.|last2=Jeger|first2=Rujana}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=munoz2009>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02067.x|title=Ecological factors drive differentiation in wolves from British Columbia|journal=Journal of Biogeography|volume=36|issue=8|pages=1516\u20131531|year=2009|last1=Mu\u00f1oz-Fuentes|first1=Violeta|last2=Darimont|first2=Chris T.|last3=Wayne|first3=Robert K.|last4=Paquet|first4=Paul C.|last5=Leonard|first5=Jennifer A.|hdl=10261/61670|hdl-access=free}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=musiani2007>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1365-294X.2007.03458.x|pmid=17725575|title=Differentiation of tundra/taiga and boreal coniferous forest wolves: Genetics, coat colour and association with migratory caribou|journal=Molecular Ecology|volume=16|issue=19|pages=4149\u201370|year=2007|last1=Musiani|first1=Marco|last2=Leonard|first2=Jennifer A.|last3=Cluff|first3=H. Dean|last4=Gates|first4=C. Cormack|last5=Mariani|first5=Stefano|last6=Paquet|first6=Paul C.|last7=Vil\u00e0|first7=Carles|last8=Wayne|first8=Robert K.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=nature2015>{{cite journal|journal=Nature|year=2015|title=Ancient wolf genome pushes back dawn of the dog| url=http://www.nature.